  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nWhen sending ETH to contract we default Gas Limit to 21000 Gwei which makes all such transactions to fail. \r\nMetamask, for instance, fetches correctly gas limit in such cases. \r\n(originally reported by user. E.g. of transaction https://etherscan.io/tx/0x4fc443416aa46126f9fda6505c77292e21ea255c6da521195a66ff160640490f)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nGas Limit fetched from network when sending ETH to contract\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nGas Limit always 21000 when sending ETH to contract\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/133415300-e12dd001-43b6-4ceb-aa52-6e4d77f1502d.mov\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) Open Status and recover an account with ETH\r\n2) Open `Wallet` -> `Send`\r\n3) Enter valid ETH value\r\n4) `Choose recipient` -> enter `0x90d39be061c135814426b12227456b36e0fe6b77`. Accept warning notifying 'You are about to send to contract' -> `Done`\r\n5) Tap `Next` \r\n6) Open `Network Fee` details and check Gas Limit value\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: release/nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
